</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulothraem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lothraem</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.delharen.com/images/sword.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/7/02 7:36:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2499.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestion on dealing with EXP loss in arena battles</span><hr size=1> My old guild and I fought and dueled in the arena extensively. My guild was very heavy with Necro's and SK's. I am speaking from several years of experience fighting in the arena on a regular (monthly) basis.<br>
<br>
You cannot lose exp inside the arena. Period. Not from a DoT or a Pet. The only time you will lose exp is if you leave the arena while dotted or with a pet chasing you and then die outside the walls. IMPORTANT The arena is only inside the walls of the arena propper! The surrounding circle outside the walls is NOT the arena and you CAN lose exp if you die inside the zone, but outside the arena walls.<br>
<br>
Same goes for any other arena large or small. As long as you stay within the area that says &quot;You have entered a pvp area&quot; then you are safe so long as you dont leave while dotted or get chased out by someones pet.<br>
<br>
So enjoy yerself and no worries!<br>
<br>
Duels outside of the arena are an entirely different matter. If you die of a DoT or a Pet in a duel, outside of an arena, you will deffinately lose exp as the game cannot differintiate between a players DoT or an NPC DoT. It only knows a DoT killed you. If this bothers you, don't duel outside an arena against a dot/pet class. But please don't ask the player to not use their pet/dots. Thats like asking to fight a kick boxer who has a broken leg. Unfair to them and demeaning to yourself. <p>"The only future in peace, is War."  - Lothraem L'Velve </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ulothraem.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lothraem</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.delharen.com/images/sword.gif" BORDER=0> at: 8/7/02 7:46:42 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uczakoriah.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Czakoriah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 35<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/8/02 6:17:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2499.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestion on dealing with EXP loss in arena battles</span><hr size=1> Awesome....No Restrictions...other than not leaving the PvP area!  Let the games begin....<br>
